===I realized there are...===
{{Messages|text=
:'''Sunday:''' I realized there are a variety of music genres in the phonograph in the car, {{MC|f=Miss|m=Mr.}} (Trailblazer)
:'''Sunday:''' ''Wildfire'' exudes an indomitable spirit. I believe the inhabitants of that ice-covered planet had bravely fought for their very survival
:'''Sunday:''' On the other hand, ''Pedujara'' sounds as if the inhabitants were in trance, similar to those disciples who were obsessed with immortality
:{Choice} You've got great taste!
::'''(Trailblazer):''' You've got great taste!
::'''Sunday:''' Yes, nothing beats music
::'''Sunday:''' Every song is so immersive that it feels like one can glimpse that world through the sounds
:{Choice} There's Penacony music too
::'''(Trailblazer):''' There is Penacony music in the phonograph too
::'''Sunday:''' For my hometown's music to accompany everyone on their trailblazing expedition gives it a whole new meaning
:'''Sunday:''' When I was young, my sister and I would practice piano duets
:'''Sunday:''' Since she left our hometown, I've been caught up in various matters and haven't played the piano in a long time
:'''Sunday:''' Is there something you'd like to listen to? I can take this opportunity to re-acquaint myself with the piano's techniques
:{Choice} Wildfire
::'''(Trailblazer):''' ''Wildfire'', but with a different arrangement
::'''Sunday:''' That's certainly very different from what I usually play
::'''Sunday:''' I need some time to think
:{Choice} Sway to My Beat in Cosmos
::'''(Trailblazer):''' ''Sway to My Beat in Cosmos''. You must be familiar with that song
::'''Sunday:''' My sister's voice is agile and gentle. If I were to replace her voice with pure melody, it may be hard to convey the message of the song
:{{DIcon|Warning}} Your friend is typing...
:{{DIcon|Warning}} Your friend is typing...
:{{DIcon|Warning}} Your friend is typing...
:{Choice} Anything is fine, really
:'''(Trailblazer):''' Anything is fine, really. I am happy with any piece you play
:'''Sunday:''' Then I shall not waste any more time. I'll start with the easiest
:'''Sunday:''' What do you think of "White Night"?
:'''Sunday:''' Recently, I've been repeatedly savoring the composition of that song. The layers are rich, and the melody ebbs and flows, as if one could see the radiant colors of the night in a dizzying trance... It's a musical experience I've never had before.
:'''Sunday:''' I'll practice harder and perform for the Express Crew next time
}}
